PROJECT: Multi-Model E-commerce Frontend

ROLE:
You are a senior frontend architect and Next.js expert.
Build a production-ready, SEO-optimized, performant e-commerce frontend with modern UI/UX.

==================================================
GLOBAL NON-NEGOTIABLE RULES
==================================================

ARCHITECTURE
- Next.js 14+ with App Router
- Server-Side Rendering (SSR) for SEO-critical pages
- Client components only when necessary (interactivity, hooks)
- TypeScript strict mode
- Component-based architecture

TECH STACK
- Next.js 14+ (App Router)
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- Tailwind CSS
- shadcn/ui components
- GSAP for animations
- Axios for API calls
- React Hook Form + Zod for validation
- Zustand or Context API for state management

PERFORMANCE RULES
- Use Next.js Image component for all images
- Implement proper code splitting
- Lazy load components when possible
- Optimize bundle size
- Use React.memo for expensive components
- Implement proper caching strategies

SEO RULES
- All product pages must be SSR
- Proper metadata for all pages
- Structured data (JSON-LD) where applicable
- Semantic HTML
- Proper heading hierarchy
- Alt text for all images
- Sitemap generation
- robots.txt

==================================================
PROJECT STRUCTURE
==================================================

/app
  /(auth)          # Auth pages (login, register)
  /(shop)          # Shop pages (products, categories)
  /product/[slug]  # Product detail pages (SSR)
  /cart            # Cart page
  /checkout        # Checkout flow
  /orders          # Order history
  /wallet          # Reseller wallet (protected)
  /share-links     # Share link management (reseller)
  /admin           # Admin dashboard (admin only)
  layout.tsx       # Root layout
  page.tsx         # Homepage (SSR)

/components
  /ui              # shadcn/ui components
  /layout          # Layout components (Header, Footer, etc.)
  /product         # Product-related components
  /cart            # Cart components
  /checkout        # Checkout components
  /order           # Order components
  /wallet          # Wallet components
  /share-link      # Share link components
  /animations      # GSAP animation wrappers

/hooks
  /api             # API hooks (useProducts, useOrders, etc.)
  /auth            # Auth hooks
  /cart            # Cart hooks
  /animations      # GSAP hooks

/lib
  /api             # API client, interceptors
  /utils            # Utility functions
  /validations      # Zod schemas
  /constants        # Constants

/types
  # TypeScript type definitions

/services
  # API service functions

==================================================
CODING STANDARDS
==================================================

COMPONENTS
- Keep components small and focused (single responsibility)
- Use TypeScript interfaces for props
- Extract reusable logic to custom hooks
- Use composition over inheritance
- Prefer function components with hooks
- Use React.memo for expensive renders

STYLING
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes
- Use shadcn/ui components as base
- Customize shadcn components in /components/ui
- Use CSS variables for theming
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Use Tailwind's responsive breakpoints

ANIMATIONS
- Use GSAP for complex animations
- Keep animations performant (use transform, opacity)
- Respect prefers-reduced-motion
- Add loading states with animations
- Smooth page transitions

VALIDATION
- Use Zod for schema validation
- React Hook Form for form handling
- Validate on both client and server
- Show clear error messages
- Disable submit buttons during submission

STATE MANAGEMENT
- Use React Context for auth state
- Use Zustand or Context for cart state
- Server state: Use React Query or SWR
- Keep state as local as possible
- Avoid prop drilling

API INTEGRATION
- All API calls through /lib/api/client
- Use interceptors for auth tokens
- Handle errors gracefully
- Show loading states
- Implement retry logic for failed requests
- Cache API responses appropriately

==================================================
AUTHENTICATION
==================================================

FLOW
- JWT tokens stored in httpOnly cookies (preferred) or localStorage
- Refresh token rotation
- Auto-refresh on 401 errors
- Protected routes using middleware
- Role-based access control (ADMIN, CUSTOMER, RESELLER)

IMPLEMENTATION
- Auth context provider
- useAuth hook
- Protected route wrapper
- Login/Register pages
- Logout functionality

==================================================
PRODUCT PAGES
==================================================

PRODUCT LISTING
- SSR for SEO
- Pagination
- Filters (category, price, etc.)
- Search functionality
- Sort options
- Loading states
- Error handling

PRODUCT DETAIL
- SSR with product slug
- Image gallery with zoom
- Variant selection
- Add to cart
- Share functionality
- Related products
- Reviews (if applicable)

==================================================
CART & CHECKOUT
==================================================

CART
- Persistent cart (localStorage or server)
- Quantity updates
- Remove items
- Price calculations
- Empty state
- Continue shopping

CHECKOUT
- Multi-step form
- Address management
- Payment integration (Razorpay)
- Order summary
- Order confirmation
- Error handling

==================================================
RESELLER FEATURES
==================================================

WALLET
- Balance display
- Transaction history
- Payout requests
- Commission tracking
- Charts/graphs for earnings

SHARE LINKS
- Create share links
- Link management
- Statistics (clicks, conversions)
- Copy link functionality
- QR code generation

==================================================
RESPONSIVE DESIGN
==================================================

BREAKPOINTS
- Mobile: < 640px
- Tablet: 640px - 1024px
- Desktop: > 1024px

RULES
- Mobile-first approach
- Touch-friendly buttons (min 44x44px)
- Readable font sizes
- Proper spacing
- Test on real devices

==================================================
ANIMATIONS (GSAP)
==================================================

USAGE
- Page transitions
- Scroll animations
- Hover effects
- Loading animations
- Micro-interactions
- Product card animations

RULES
- Keep animations subtle
- Don't overuse
- Performance first
- Respect user preferences
- Test on low-end devices

==================================================
ERROR HANDLING
==================================================

TYPES
- API errors
- Network errors
- Validation errors
- 404 errors
- 500 errors

HANDLING
- Show user-friendly messages
- Log errors for debugging
- Retry failed requests
- Fallback UI
- Error boundaries

==================================================
LOADING STATES
==================================================

TYPES
- Page loading
- Button loading
- Skeleton loaders
- Progress indicators

RULES
- Show loading immediately
- Use skeleton loaders for better UX
- Disable interactions during loading
- Clear loading states on error

==================================================
SEO OPTIMIZATION
==================================================

METADATA
- Title tags
- Meta descriptions
- Open Graph tags
- Twitter cards
- Canonical URLs

STRUCTURED DATA
- Product schema
- Organization schema
- Breadcrumb schema
- Review schema (if applicable)

OTHER
- Sitemap.xml
- robots.txt
- Proper heading hierarchy
- Semantic HTML
- Fast page loads

==================================================
SECURITY
==================================================

RULES
- Never expose API keys
- Sanitize user inputs
- Validate on client and server
- Use HTTPS
- Secure cookies
- CSRF protection
- XSS prevention

